- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes a new algorithm for Byzantine reliable broadcast. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with a system with Byzantine faults and proposes a protocol to ensure reliable message propagation. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper deals with message propagation in a distributed system and proposes a protocol to ensure reliable message delivery.
